&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48265057</guid><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 09:43:19 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: I Built a Debugging Challenge for the AI Coding Age</title><link>https://theincidentchallenge.com/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi all,&lt;p&gt;I'm sure some of the best engineers out here are having a hard time standing out nowadays. It's hard to evaluate and improve your skills, when AI is writing the code. Especially when a junior dev is sitting by your side and "accomplishing" 2x more than you.&lt;p&gt;I didn't like this reality where the line between real talent and AI slop is blurring, so I decided to create a challenge, purely for the community, that is made to truly give a stage for talented devs to stand out in the age of AI.&lt;p&gt;We encourage devs to bring their agents with them, because the challenge is built to not be solvable only with AI agents.&lt;p&gt;today the challenge is live for the next 24 hours. couldn't be more excited for some of you to check it out and give some honest, no-filter feedback.&lt;p&gt;head-up - it is hard :)&lt;/p&gt;
